column4: PRESS DIGEST - Wall Street Journal - Oct 16
column5: Oct 16 The following are the top stories in the Wall Street Journal. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

column4: U.S. Senate bill could give Tesla  GM electric car tax credit boost
column5: WASHINGTON  Oct 16 Tesla Inc and General Motors Co  which have lobbied Congress to lift a cap on electric vehicles eligible for a $7 500 tax credit  could get their way for up to four years under a new proposal from a Republican senator.

column4: U.S. judge approves SEC settlement with Tesla  Musk;  shares jump
column5: A U.S. judge on Tuesday approved a settlement between a federal regulator  Tesla Inc and its chief executive officer  Elon Musk  over his tweets promising to take the company private  signalling an end to a tumultuous period for investors. | Video

column4: Qualcomm  FTC ask judge to delay ruling to pursue settlement
column5: Qualcomm Inc and the U.S. Federal Trade Commission on Monday asked a federal judge to delay a preliminary ruling in an antitrust case U.S. regulators brought against the mobile chip company in order to pursue settlement talks.
